\end_inset

, there exists a 
\begin_inset Formula $N\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

 s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{n}\geq M$
\end_inset

, then for the 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 above
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left|f\left(x_{n}\right)-L\right|\geq\varepsilon
\]

\end_inset

which contradicts that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{n\to\infty}f\left(x_{n}\right)=L$
